Program: The Forum
Title: Time to Rethink What is 'Normal'?
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p022qhl1
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 21 Jul 2014
Where is the dividing line between ‘being a bit different’ and having a mental illness that needs treatment and professional help? Bridget Kendall is joined by novelist Jerry Pinto, who has turned personal experiences of growing up with a bipolar relative into an award-winning book, Professor of Disability and Human Development Lennard Davis, and autism research pioneer Professor Uta Frith. (Photo: Shan Pillay/ BBC) Show less